stories.title: A fusillade of egg curry
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v England, 2nd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: Andrew Miller samples to delights of the day-night match in Dhaka, and finds out that it's not just at Lord's the gatemen are jobsworths

stories.title: Flintoff fixes it for England ... again
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v England, 2nd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: England wrapped up an ultimately simple victory at the Bangabandhu Stadium in Dhaka, winning by seven wickets with 22.3 overs to spare after restricting Bangladesh to an inadequate 134 for 9
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Steven Lynch

stories.title: A touch of the Forrest Gumps
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v England, 2nd ODI, Dhaka
stories.summary: Another day, another defeat for Bangladesh, whose performances have completely run out of steam after the comparative heroics of the Test series
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by Andrew Miller
